exercises.problem_statement:
Write a C program to compare areas of three rectangles and find the largest using functions and a structure. Define the following typedef:

typedef struct {
    char name[50];
    float length;
    float width;
    float area;
} Rectangle;

Each rectangle is read using input(), its area computed by calculate_area(), and the largest identified by compare_areas() using an else-if ladder.

Write a C program using array of structures and functions to:
i.  Accept the number of rectangles n from the user.
ii. For each rectangle, accept its length and width.
iii. Calculate and display the area of each rectangle.
iv. Determine and display the rectangle with the largest area.

Use the following typedef:

typedef struct {
    float length;
    float width;
    float area;
} Rectangle;

Write a modular C program to manage flight records. Create a structure Flight with fields: flight_number (char[10]), destination (char[50]), available_seats (int). Create an array of 4 flights. Read flight details from the user, then accept a destination name and search for a matching flight, displaying the flight number if found.

typedef struct {
    char flight_number[10];
    char destination[50];
    int available_seats;
} Flight_t;

Write a modular C program to perform the following tasks using file handling:
i.  Read the details of n students (name, roll_no, gpa) from the user and store them in an array of structures.
ii. Write the array of structures to a text (ASCII) file using fprintf().
iii. Read the data back from the ASCII file into a second array using fscanf() and display it.

typedef struct {
    char name[50];
    int roll_no;
    float gpa;
} Student;
